---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service" description="Quiet The Mowers terms of service.">

<article class="section">
  <div class="container-narrow">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-display font-bold text-brand-900 mb-8">Terms of Service</h1>
    <div class="prose">

      <p><em>Last updated: April 2026</em></p>

      <h2>1. Acceptance</h2>
      <p>By using QuietTheMowers.com, you agree to these terms. If you do not agree, please do not use the platform.</p>

      <h2>2. The Platform</h2>
      <p>Quiet The Mowers is a civic-tech platform that provides tools for community organizing, petition creation, noise measurement, and advocacy. The platform facilitates civic engagement but does not provide legal advice.</p>

      <h2>3. User Conduct</h2>
      <p>When using the platform, you agree:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>To provide accurate information when signing petitions</li>
        <li>Not to use the platform for harassment, spam, or illegal purposes</li>
        <li>Not to submit false or misleading measurement data</li>
        <li>To respect other users and engage constructively in discussions</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Campaigns & Petitions</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Organizers are responsible for the content of their campaigns.</li>
        <li>Quiet The Mowers does not endorse any specific campaign, organizer, or policy position.</li>
        <li>We reserve the right to remove campaigns that violate these terms.</li>
        <li>Petition signature counts are public and verifiable.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Measurement Data</h2>
      <p>Noise measurements uploaded to the platform are for advocacy and awareness purposes. They may not meet the standards required for legal evidence. Users should not rely on platform-hosted measurements as the sole basis for legal proceedings without independent verification.</p>

      <h2>6. Device Rental Program</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Rental devices remain the property of Quiet The Mowers.</li>
        <li>Users are responsible for the device during the rental period and must return it by the agreed date.</li>
        <li>Lost or damaged devices may be subject to replacement fees.</li>
        <li>Calibration is best-effort. Users should verify calibration status before use in formal settings.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>The ordinance library, measurement protocol, campaign templates, and shareable assets are made available for public use. You may adapt them for your own advocacy. Attribution is appreciated but not required.</p>

      <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>Quiet The Mowers provides the platform "as is." We are not liable for the outcomes of campaigns, the accuracy of user-submitted data, or decisions made by government bodies based on platform content.</p>

      <h2>9. Moderation</h2>
      <p>We moderate testimonials, comments, and campaigns to maintain a constructive community. We may remove content that violates our moderation policy. Repeated violations may result in account suspension.</p>

      <h2>10. Changes</h2>
      <p>We may update these terms. Significant changes will be communicated via email to registered users.</p>

      <h2>11. Contact</h2>
      <p>For legal inquiries, contact legal@quietthemowers.com.</p>

    </div>
  </div>
</article>

</Layout>
